==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Lupulin
<hw>Lu"pu*lin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>lupulin</ets>. See <er>Lupuline</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A bitter principle extracted from
hops.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The fine yellow resinous powder found upon the
strobiles or fruit of hops, and containing this bitter principle.</def>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>lupuline</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lupuline</ent>⟦br⟧
